<ReportItem port="13" svc_name="daytime" protocol="udp" severity="0" pluginID="10052" pluginName="Daytime Service Detection" pluginFamily="Service detection">
<description>The remote host is running a &apos;daytime&apos; service.  This service is designed to give the local time of the day of this host to whoever connects to this port.  The date format issued by this service may sometimes help an attacker to guess the operating system type of this host, or to set up timed authentication attacks against the remote host. 

In addition, if the daytime service is running on a UDP port, an attacker may link it to the echo port of a third-party host using spoofing, thus creating a possible denial of service condition between this host and the third party.</description>
